		<h2>Logo</h2>

		<p>The logo is composed of two elements Font Awesome <i class="fa fa-plus"></i> and the text <span class="logo-font">CheckMed</span>.  When <span class="logo-font">CheckMed</span> is shown in the footer there is no need for the Font Awesome <i class="fa fa-plus"></i> icon.  Below is an example of the structure required for the logo and call to action treatment.  Notice the call-to-action text is hidden when there is not parent element class of .justLanded present.</p>

		<pre style="background-color: #eee;padding: 1em;">
